"The general assumption is that:\n. a health station (CHW) serves 500-3,000 people & Real needs are generally much greater in emergencies than in normal situations, due to the development of needs specific to the disaster (wounded) and to the particularly harsh environmental conditions to which the victims are subject (lack of food, cold, etc.). & The geographical factor may be simplified, insofar as the refugee population is housed in a clearly delimited camp, so that the health-care facilities are immediately accessible."